cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with training a Convolutional Neural Network to assign a canonical orientation to feature points in images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new type of activation function for Neural Networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Siamese networks for finding optimal orientations during training suggests the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of existing rotation-sensitive descriptors, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the validation of the method on existing datasets and the creation of a new dataset suggests the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
